underlying_goal: To design an API response caching layer for cost savings.
primary_success: Guiding the design of the caching mechanism from requirements to a specific implementation, including selecting the best data structure (in-memory dict) and persistence format (JSONL) based on trade-offs.
brief_summary: The user asked to plan and add an API response cache. Through a brainstorming session, Claude helped define the goal, choose a storage mechanism (in-memory dict with JSONL persistence), and design the cache key strategy and a Python cache class.
